  "title": "IT Operations and Project Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>IT Operations and Project Manager</strong><br /></p><p><strong>Scope:</strong></p><ul><li>Work closely with various airport stakeholders, both internal and external, to gather user requirements and deliver solutions to the users.</li><li>Work with internal technical teams and vendors to propose overall technical solutions and key performance indicators to measure success.</li><li>Perform proper project and change management to ensure delivered solutions meet technical, functional, performance, and business requirements.</li><li>Manage 24/7 operations, maintenance, compliance, and renewal of our Airport IT systems to support operations of the airport. Candidates who are cognisant with industry best practices are preferred.</li><li>Perform, review, and enhance business and IT processes as part of the continuous improvement effort.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>An accredited <strong>Bachelor’s degree </strong>in Information Systems / Technology, Computer Science, Systems Engineering, or related discipline.</li><li>Certifications in IT Service Management (ITSM) or IT Project Management is an advantage</li><li>Demonstrated knowledge in <strong>Networking, System Administration, and Cyber Security</strong>.</li><li>Minimum three years of work experience in the related technical domains and industry.</li><li>Strong analytical and project management skills.</li></ul>",
